detaileddescription.para:
The definition here is for clarity, as it makes code more self documenting. Imagine this: unsignedintgetSize() By using this definition, that code becomes: SizegetSize() Not only is it shorter, but it makes it more obvious, making documentation easier.

Enum

memberdef.definition: using mc::Index = typedef unsigned int
memberdef.name: Index

briefdescription.para: Type representing an index in an array.

detaileddescription.para:
The definition here is for clarity, and it makes code more obvious and self-documenting. Imagine this: removeObject(unsignedint) or getObject(unsignedint) unsigned int is ambigious! What if the object is an unsigned int? With this definition, it becomes much more clear: removeObject(Index)
getObject(Index)

briefdescription.para: Exception thrown when a syntax error is encountered, or #error is called.

detaileddescription.para: The filename and line number will be in message.
